Note:
C++ Parser - Recursive-descent parser building a C++ AST from the token stream.

Parses C++17 constructs: preprocessor directive passthrough, namespaces
(including nested and using), classes/structs/unions/enums (incl. enum class)
with access specifiers and inheritance (virtual/override/final), templates
(type/non-type/template-template params), members (fields, methods, ctors,
dtors, operators, friend), storage/qualifiers, statements (if/else, for,
range-for, while, do, switch/case, try/catch, return, throw), and full C++
expression precedence (assignment, ternary, ||, &&, bitwise, equality,
relational, spaceship, shift, additive, multiplicative, unary, cast, new/delete,
sizeof, scope ::, member ./->, calls, subscript, lambdas, literals).

Forward-progress contract: every statement/member/declaration loop reads the
lexer byte cursor before and after a sub-parser; if the sub-parser consumed no
bytes the loop force-advances one token and records an error, so a malformed
token can never spin the parser. This is the exact guard the C# precedent
required.

Dependencies:
- cpp_lexer.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/cpp/cpp_lexer.runa" as Lexer
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List

