Constant CPP_POINTER_TYPE as Integer is 71
Constant CPP_REFERENCE_TYPE as Integer is 72
Constant CPP_ARRAY_TYPE as Integer is 73
Constant CPP_FUNCTION_TYPE as Integer is 74
Constant CPP_TEMPLATE_TYPE as Integer is 75
Constant CPP_AUTO_TYPE as Integer is 76

Note: Template parameter kind tags (stored in value slot)
Constant TOKEN_TYPENAME as Integer is 46
Constant TOKEN_CLASS as Integer is 40

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AST Node Structure
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
One AST node type spans expressions, statements, declarations and types because
C++ shares operators across all four families. node_type disambiguates the role;
name/value/type_info/children/attributes/template_params are populated
selectively. A 72-byte record keeps every node a uniform shape so visitor passes
can read slots unconditionally.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
9 x i64 at offsets 0..64: node_type (0), name (8: owned identifier copy or 0),
value (16: owned operator/literal text or numeric tag or 0), type_info (24:
type-node pointer or 0), children (32: List of child nodes or 0), attributes
(40: packed flags / access level / numeric attribute), template_params (48: List
of param nodes or 0), line (56), column (64).
@End Implementation

Type called "CppASTNode":
    node_type as Integer
    name as Integer
    value as Integer
    type_info as Integer
    children as Integer
    attributes as Integer
    template_params as Integer
    line as Integer
    column as Integer
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Parser State
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Single-lookahead recursive-descent parser. current_token caches the lookahead
type so peek is O(1); current_class supports constructor/destructor recognition
in member parsing; template_depth disambiguates nested template angle brackets;
error_message/has_error provide sticky first-error reporting.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
6 x i64 at offsets 0..40: lexer (0), current_token (8), error_message (16),
has_error (24), current_class (32), template_depth (40).
@End Implementation

Type called "CppParser":
    lexer as Integer
    current_token as Integer
    error_message as Integer
    has_error as Integer
    current_class as Integer
    template_depth as Integer
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Parser Creation and Destruction
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Allocates the 48-byte CppParser, builds the underlying CppLexer, and primes the
lookahead with the first token so peek_token_type works immediately.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Layout.allocate(48); OOM returns 0. create_cpp_lexer on the source; on failure
frees the parser and returns 0. Zeroes current_token/error/has_error/
current_class/template_depth then calls advance_token to load the first token.
@End Implementation

Process called "create_cpp_parser" takes source as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create C++ parser from source code

    Let parser be proc allocate from Layout with 48
    If parser is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let lexer be proc create_cpp_lexer from Lexer with source
    If lexer is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with parser
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 0, lexer
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 24, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 32, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 40, 0

    proc advance_token with parser

    Return parser
End Process

@Reasoning:
Symmetric teardown. Owns the lexer and any error_message copy; AST nodes are
independent of parser lifetime.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null parser short-circuits with success. Destroys the lexer if present, frees the
error_message copy if present, then frees the 48-byte record. Returns 1.
@End Implementation

Process called "destroy_cpp_parser" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Destroy C++ parser and free resources

    If parser is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let lexer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 0
    If lexer is not equal to 0:
        proc destroy_cpp_lexer from Lexer with lexer
    End If

    Let error_message be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 16
    If error_message is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with error_message
    End If

    proc deallocate from Layout with parser
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AST Node Helpers
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Centralised zero-initialised node allocator so every parse path produces nodes
with the same slot layout; "0 == unset" holds for every slot.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 72 bytes, writes node_type at offset 0, zeroes the other eight slots.
Returns 0 on OOM.
@End Implementation

Process called "create_cpp_ast_node" takes node_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create C++ AST node of given type

    Let node be proc allocate from Layout with 72
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 0, node_type
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 24, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 32, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 40, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 48, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 56, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 64, 0

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Children list is created lazily so leaf nodes never pay for an empty List.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-checks parent and child. Reads children slot (offset 32); allocates a fresh
List if 0; pushes child. Ownership of child transfers to parent.
@End Implementation

Process called "add_child_to_cpp_ast_node" takes parent as Integer, child as Integer:
    Note: Add child node to parent's children list

    If parent is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    If child is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parent, 32
    If children is equal to 0:
        Set children to proc create from List
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parent, 32, children
    End If

    proc push from List with children, child
End Process

@Reasoning:
Names are user-controlled identifier text needed by later passes; the node owns
its own copy so the lexer's lexeme buffer can be recycled.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-checks node; copies the name via StringCore.string_duplicate and stores the
copy at offset 8.
@End Implementation

Process called "set_cpp_ast_node_name" takes node as Integer, name as Integer:
    Note: Set AST node name (owned copy)

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let name_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringCore with name
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 8, name_copy
End Process

@Reasoning:
Stores an already-owned name string directly into the node's name slot, taking
ownership without re-duplicating. Used for the result of parse_qualified_name,
which already returns an owned copy - re-duplicating it would leak the original.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-checks node and name; writes the name handle verbatim at offset 8.
@End Implementation

Process called "set_cpp_ast_node_name_owned" takes node as Integer, name as Integer:
    Note: Store an owned name directly (no re-duplication)

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 8, name
End Process

@Reasoning:
The value slot holds operator strings, literal text, or numeric tags. Stored
verbatim because callers pass either an owned copy or a numeric tag.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-checks node; writes value at offset 16.
@End Implementation

Process called "set_cpp_ast_node_value" takes node as Integer, value as Integer:
    Note: Set AST node value verbatim

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 16, value
End Process

@Reasoning:
Convenience setter that copies a lexeme into the value slot as owned text - used
for operator and literal lexemes the node must outlive.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-checks node; if value non-zero copies via string_duplicate; stores at
offset 16.
@End Implementation

Process called "set_cpp_ast_node_value_text" takes node as Integer, value as Integer:
    Note: Set AST node value as an owned text copy

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    Let copy be proc string_duplicate from StringCore with value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 16, copy
End Process

@Reasoning:
Access level (private/protected/public) stamped on members so the semantic and
HIR layers can apply access control without re-walking to the class scope.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Writes the access constant into the attributes slot at offset 40.
@End Implementation

Process called "set_cpp_ast_node_access_level" takes node as Integer, access as Integer:
    Note: Set access level for class member

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 40, access
End Process

@Reasoning:
Template parameter lists attached to template-declaration nodes so HIR emission
can reproduce the template prefix.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-checks node; writes the param-list handle at offset 48.
@End Implementation

Process called "set_cpp_ast_node_template_params" takes node as Integer, params as Integer:
    Note: Set template parameters for node

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 48, params
End Process

@Reasoning:
type_info slot holds a node's declared type (a CPP_TYPE_NODE subtree). Stored
verbatim because the type node is already owned.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-checks node; writes the type node at offset 24.
@End Implementation

Process called "set_cpp_ast_node_type_info" takes node as Integer, type_node as Integer:
    Note: Set AST node declared type

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 24, type_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Read-only name accessor returning the owned copy; returns 0 for null nodes so
visitors chain without null-checking.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-check then returns the handle at offset 8.
@End Implementation

Process called "get_cpp_ast_node_name" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get AST node name

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 8
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Token Management
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Single-token-of-lookahead advance. Caches the next token type at offset 8 so
peek_token_type is O(1).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Loads lexer (offset 0), calls Lexer.next_token, stores the result at offset 8.
@End Implementation

Process called "advance_token" takes parser as Integer:
    Note: Advance to next token

    Let lexer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 0
    Let next be proc next_token from Lexer with lexer
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 8, next
End Process

@Reasoning:
Read-only accessor for the lookahead token type.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Single memory_get_int64 from offset 8.
@End Implementation

Process called "peek_token_type" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Current lookahead token type

    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 8
End Process

@Reasoning:
The token text lives on the lexer; bridges to current_lexeme without affecting
the lookahead.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the lexer (offset 0) and returns Lexer.current_lexeme (a borrowed pointer).
@End Implementation

Process called "peek_token_lexeme" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Current token lexeme (borrowed)

    Let lexer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 0
    Return proc current_lexeme from Lexer with lexer
End Process

@Reasoning:
The lexer's byte cursor is the forward-progress oracle. Loops read it before and
after a sub-parser; equality means no progress and the loop must force-advance.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the lexer (offset 0) and returns its position field (offset 16).
@End Implementation

Process called "lexer_position" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Current lexer byte cursor (forward-progress oracle)

    Let lexer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 0
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 16
End Process

@Reasoning:
Match-or-error combinator. Advancing only on match leaves the cursor on the
offending token for diagnostics.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Compares peek against expected. Match advances; mismatch sets the sticky error.
@End Implementation

Process called "expect_token" takes parser as Integer, expected as Integer, message as Integer:
    Note: Expect a token type or set the sticky error

    Let current_type be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If current_type is equal to expected:
        proc advance_token with parser
    Otherwise:
        proc set_parse_error with parser, message
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Sticky error setter used by every expectation. Stores a parser-owned copy of the
message so the caller's handle is not aliased.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Writes has_error=1 (offset 24) and an owned copy of message (string_duplicate) at
offset 16. First-error-wins is enforced by callers checking has_error.
@End Implementation

Process called "set_parse_error" takes parser as Integer, message as Integer:
    Note: Set sticky parser error

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 24, 1
    Let copy be proc string_duplicate from StringCore with message
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 16, copy
End Process

@Reasoning:
Sticky-flag accessor for combinators that branch on success/failure.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads has_error at offset 24.
@End Implementation

Process called "has_parse_error" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Whether the parser has latched an error

    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 24
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Token Predicates
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Type-keyword predicate: detects a declaration-specifier lead so the top-level and
member loops can route into parse_declaration. Covers builtin type keywords,
storage/qualifier keywords, and a plain identifier (user type name).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Returns 1 for the builtin type tokens (VOID..WCHAR_T), the storage/qualifier
tokens (CONST..REGISTER, CONSTEXPR, INLINE, VIRTUAL, STATIC, EXTERN, EXPLICIT,
FRIEND, MUTABLE, VOLATILE), TYPENAME, and IDENTIFIER; else 0.
@End Implementation

Process called "is_type_start" takes token_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Whether token begins a declaration specifier / type

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_VOID from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_BOOL from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CHAR from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_SHORT from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_INT from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LONG from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_FLOAT from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_DOUBLE from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_SIGNED from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_UNSIGNED from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_AUTO from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_WCHAR_T from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CONST from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CONSTEXPR from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_VOLATILE from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_MUTABLE from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_STATIC from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_EXTERN from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_INLINE from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_REGISTER from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_VIRTUAL from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_EXPLICIT from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_FRIEND from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_TYPENAME from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Storage/qualifier predicate used by the declaration-specifier loop to absorb
leading modifiers before the core type.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Returns 1 for the storage/qualifier tokens; else 0.
@End Implementation

Process called "is_qualifier" takes token_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Whether token is a storage class or cv-qualifier

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CONST from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CONSTEXPR from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_VOLATILE from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_MUTABLE from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_STATIC from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_EXTERN from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_INLINE from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_REGISTER from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_VIRTUAL from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_EXPLICIT from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_FRIEND from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Main Parsing Entry Point
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Top-level recursive-descent dispatch. C++ admits namespace, class, struct, union,
enum, template, using, typedef, preprocessor, function, and global variable
file-scope productions. Loops until TOKEN_EOF. A forward-progress guard
force-advances if any iteration consumes no bytes so malformed input cannot spin
the loop.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates a CPP_PROGRAM root. Loop peeks the cursor: EOF breaks. Branches by token
kind to the specialist parse_* routine and appends non-null results. Reads the
lexer byte cursor before and after each iteration; if equal it sets an error and
advances one token. On sticky error returns the partial program (so the test can
still inspect what parsed). Returns the program node on clean EOF.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_cpp_program" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse an entire C++ translation unit

    Let program_node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_PROGRAM

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        Let before be proc lexer_position with parser

        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PREPROCESSOR from Lexer:
            Let pp be proc parse_preprocessor_directive with parser
            If pp is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with program_node, pp
            End If
            Continue
        End If
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_NAMESPACE from Lexer:
            Let ns be proc parse_namespace_declaration with parser
            If ns is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with program_node, ns
            End If
            Continue
        End If
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_TEMPLATE from Lexer:
            Let tpl be proc parse_template_declaration with parser
            If tpl is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with program_node, tpl
            End If
            Continue
        End If
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CLASS from Lexer:
            Let cls be proc parse_class_declaration with parser
            If cls is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with program_node, cls
            End If
            Continue
        End If
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_STRUCT from Lexer:
            Let st be proc parse_struct_declaration with parser
            If st is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with program_node, st
            End If
            Continue
        End If
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_UNION from Lexer:
            Let un be proc parse_struct_declaration with parser
            If un is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with program_node, un
            End If
            Continue
        End If
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ENUM from Lexer:
            Let en be proc parse_enum_declaration with parser
            If en is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with program_node, en
            End If
            Continue
        End If
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_USING from Lexer:
            Let us be proc parse_using_declaration with parser
            If us is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with program_node, us
            End If
            Continue
        End If
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_TYPEDEF from Lexer:
            Let td be proc parse_typedef_declaration with parser
            If td is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with program_node, td
            End If
            Continue
        End If

        Let decl be proc parse_declaration with parser
        If decl is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with program_node, decl
        End If

        Let has_err be proc has_parse_error with parser
        If has_err is equal to 1:
            Return program_node
        End If

        Let after be proc lexer_position with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            Note: No forward progress - force-advance to avoid spinning
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
    End While

    Return program_node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Preprocessor / Using / Typedef
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
A preprocessor directive was lexed as one TOKEN_PREPROCESSOR. The parser records
it verbatim as a CPP_PREPROCESSOR node so HIR can round-trip #include / #define /
#ifdef etc. The directive token is consumed (advancing) so the program loop
progresses.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Captures the directive lexeme, copies it into the node value, consumes the token,
and returns the node.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_preprocessor_directive" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a preprocessor directive line

    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_PREPROCESSOR
    Let text be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
    proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with node, text
    proc advance_token with parser
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'using name = type;' (alias), 'using namespace ns;' (directive), or
'using qualified::name;' (declaration). The kind is captured in the value tag and
the alias target / qualified name as the node name; an alias target type becomes
type_info.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'using'. If next is 'namespace', records "namespace" value and the
namespace name. Otherwise captures the (possibly qualified) name; if an '=' is
seen it parses the aliased type into type_info. Consumes the trailing ';'.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_using_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a using declaration / directive / alias

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'using'
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_USING

    Let next be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If next is equal to TOKEN_NAMESPACE from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with node, "namespace"
        Let ns_name be proc parse_qualified_name with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_name_owned with node, ns_name
        proc consume_semicolon with parser
        Return node
    End If

    Let name be proc parse_qualified_name with parser
    proc set_cpp_ast_node_name_owned with node, name

    Let eq be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If eq is equal to TOKEN_ASSIGN from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with node, "alias"
        Let target be proc parse_type_specifier with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_type_info with node, target
    Otherwise:
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with node, "declaration"
    End If

    proc consume_semicolon with parser
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'typedef type name;'. The underlying type is captured as type_info and the
alias as the node name.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'typedef', parses the type specifier into type_info, captures the alias
identifier name, consumes ';'.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_typedef_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a typedef declaration

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'typedef'
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_TYPEDEF

    Let underlying be proc parse_type_specifier with parser
    proc set_cpp_ast_node_type_info with node, underlying

    Let name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
    Let nt be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If nt is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with node, name
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If

    proc consume_semicolon with parser
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Helper that consumes a trailing ';' if present without erroring on its absence -
the C++ grammar has several optional-semicolon contexts and the round-trip test
tolerates either.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Peeks; if TOKEN_SEMICOLON, advances. Otherwise no-op.
@End Implementation

Process called "consume_semicolon" takes parser as Integer:
    Note: Consume an optional trailing semicolon

    Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If t is equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a possibly-qualified name: identifier ( :: identifier )*. Returns an OWNED
duplicate of the final identifier segment. The duplicate is taken BEFORE the
advance that frees the lexer's lexeme buffer - the lexer recycles its lexeme copy
on every next_token, so a pointer captured before the advance would dangle. The
returned pointer is owned by the caller (the 7 call sites store it directly into
an AST node's name slot, transferring ownership), so this proc must never be fed
to a re-duplicating setter.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Tracks the owned copy of the most recent segment. For the lead identifier: if it
is an IDENTIFIER, duplicates the current lexeme then advances. For each '::'
suffix: advances past '::', duplicates the next identifier's lexeme (freeing the
prior segment copy), then advances. Returns the last owned segment copy, or 0 if
no identifier was present.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_qualified_name" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse identifier ( :: identifier )* ; return an OWNED copy of the final segment

    Let name be 0
    Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If t is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
        Let lexeme be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        Set name to proc string_duplicate from StringCore with lexeme
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let scope be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If scope is not equal to TOKEN_SCOPE from Lexer:
            Break
        End If
        proc advance_token with parser  Note: '::'
        Let it be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If it is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
            Let seg_lexeme be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
            Let seg_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringCore with seg_lexeme
            If name is not equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with name
            End If
            Set name to seg_copy
            proc advance_token with parser
        Otherwise:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    Return name
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Namespace Declaration
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Parses 'namespace [name] { declarations }' including nested and anonymous
namespaces. The members are parsed with the same top-level dispatch so nested
namespaces, classes, templates and functions all work inside.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'namespace'. Captures an optional name (anonymous namespace leaves the
name 0). Expects '{'. Loops parsing member declarations until '}', appending each
to the namespace node. A forward-progress guard force-advances on a
non-consuming iteration. Returns the namespace node.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_namespace_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a namespace declaration

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'namespace'
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_NAMESPACE

    Let nt be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If nt is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
        Let name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with node, name
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If

    Let brace be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If brace is not equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
        Note: namespace alias or using - consume to ';'
        proc consume_semicolon with parser
        Return node
    End If
    proc advance_token with parser  Note: '{'

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Break
        End If
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        Let before be proc lexer_position with parser
        Let member be proc parse_namespace_member with parser
        If member is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, member
        End If

        Let has_err be proc has_parse_error with parser
        If has_err is equal to 1:
            Break
        End If

        Let after be proc lexer_position with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
    End While

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
A namespace member is the same set of productions as the file scope. Factored out
so both the top-level loop and the namespace loop share routing without
duplicating the long branch chain twice over.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Branches on the lead token to namespace / template / class / struct / union /
enum / using / typedef, defaulting to parse_declaration. Mirrors
parse_cpp_program's dispatch.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_namespace_member" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a single member inside a namespace body

    Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PREPROCESSOR from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_preprocessor_directive with parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_NAMESPACE from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_namespace_declaration with parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_TEMPLATE from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_template_declaration with parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CLASS from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_class_declaration with parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_STRUCT from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_struct_declaration with parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_UNION from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_struct_declaration with parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ENUM from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_enum_declaration with parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_USING from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_using_declaration with parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_TYPEDEF from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_typedef_declaration with parser
    End If

    Return proc parse_declaration with parser
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Enum Declaration
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Parses 'enum [class|struct] Name [: underlying] { v1, v2 = expr, ... };'. enum
class / enum struct (scoped enums) set the "scoped" value tag. Each enumerator is
a CPP_ENUM_VALUE child carrying its name and an optional initializer expression.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'enum'. If 'class'/'struct' follows, consumes it and tags "scoped".
Captures the optional enum name. Optional ': underlying' sets type_info. Expects
'{'; loops capturing enumerators (name + optional '= expr') separated by commas
until '}'. Consumes the trailing ';'. Forward-progress guard inside the
enumerator loop.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_enum_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse an enum / enum class declaration

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'enum'
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_ENUM

    Let next be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If next is equal to TOKEN_CLASS from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with node, "scoped"
    Otherwise:
        If next is equal to TOKEN_STRUCT from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with node, "scoped"
        Otherwise:
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with node, "unscoped"
        End If
    End If

    Let nt be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If nt is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
        Let name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with node, name
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If

    Let colon be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If colon is equal to TOKEN_COLON from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let underlying be proc parse_type_specifier with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_type_info with node, underlying
    End If

    Let brace be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If brace is not equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
        proc consume_semicolon with parser
        Return node
    End If
    proc advance_token with parser  Note: '{'

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Break
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        Let before be proc lexer_position with parser

        If t is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
            Let ev be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_ENUM_VALUE
            Let vname be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with ev, vname
            proc advance_token with parser

            Let assign be proc peek_token_type with parser
            If assign is equal to TOKEN_ASSIGN from Lexer:
                proc advance_token with parser
                Let init be proc parse_assignment_expression with parser
                proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with ev, init
            End If

            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, ev
        End If

        Let comma be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If comma is equal to TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If

        Let after be proc lexer_position with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
    End While

    proc consume_semicolon with parser
    Return node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Class / Struct Declaration
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Parses 'class Name [final] [: base-list] { members };' (and forward
declarations). Class default access is private. Saves/restores current_class to
support nested classes so member parsing can recognise constructors.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'class', creates CPP_CLASS, captures the name. Consumes an optional
'final'. Optional inheritance (':' base-list) becomes a CPP_INHERITANCE child. A
';' here is a forward declaration. Otherwise expects '{', sets current_class,
loops members tracking the current access section (default private), restores
current_class, consumes the trailing ';'.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_class_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a class declaration / definition

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'class'
    Return proc parse_class_or_struct_body with parser, 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Structs and unions share the class body grammar but default to public access.
Routes both through the common body parser with default_access=2 (public).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes the 'struct'/'union' keyword, delegates to parse_class_or_struct_body
with public default access.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_struct_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a struct or union declaration

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'struct' / 'union'
    Return proc parse_class_or_struct_body with parser, 2
End Process

@Reasoning:
Shared body parser for class/struct/union. default_access seeds the access
section (0 private for class, 2 public for struct/union). The member loop is
guarded for forward progress.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates CPP_CLASS, captures name, consumes optional 'final', parses optional
inheritance. ';' returns a forward declaration. Otherwise consumes '{', saves
current_class, loops: '}' ends; access-specifier labels (public/private/
protected ':') update current_access; otherwise parse_class_member with the
current access. Forward-progress guard force-advances on a non-consuming
iteration. Restores current_class and consumes ';'.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_class_or_struct_body" takes parser as Integer, default_access as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Shared class/struct/union body parser

    Let class_node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_CLASS

    Let nt be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If nt is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
        Let name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with class_node, name
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If

    Let fin be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If fin is equal to TOKEN_FINAL from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If

    Let colon be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If colon is equal to TOKEN_COLON from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let inheritance be proc parse_inheritance_list with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with class_node, inheritance
    End If

    Let brace be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If brace is equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Return class_node
    End If
    If brace is not equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
        proc set_parse_error with parser, "Expected '{' or ';' in class declaration"
        Return class_node
    End If
    proc advance_token with parser  Note: '{'

    Let old_class be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 32
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 32, class_node

    Let current_access be default_access

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let member_token be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If member_token is equal to TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Break
        End If
        If member_token is equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        Let before be proc lexer_position with parser

        If member_token is equal to TOKEN_PUBLIC from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            proc consume_colon with parser
            Set current_access to 2
            Continue
        End If
        If member_token is equal to TOKEN_PRIVATE from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            proc consume_colon with parser
            Set current_access to 0
            Continue
        End If
        If member_token is equal to TOKEN_PROTECTED from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            proc consume_colon with parser
            Set current_access to 1
            Continue
        End If

        Let member be proc parse_class_member with parser, current_access
        If member is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with class_node, member
        End If

        Let has_err be proc has_parse_error with parser
        If has_err is equal to 1:
            Break
        End If

        Let after be proc lexer_position with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
    End While

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 32, old_class

    proc consume_semicolon with parser
    Return class_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Helper consuming an optional ':' after an access label.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Peeks; if TOKEN_COLON, advances.
@End Implementation

Process called "consume_colon" takes parser as Integer:
    Note: Consume an optional ':' after an access label

    Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If t is equal to TOKEN_COLON from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses the base-class list 'access? virtual? Name (, ...)*'. Each base becomes a
CPP_BASE_CLASS node carrying its name and access tag. The list is wrapped in a
CPP_INHERITANCE node.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates CPP_INHERITANCE. Loops: per base, optionally consume an access keyword
(public/private/protected) recording the access level, optionally 'virtual',
then the qualified base name. Appends a CPP_BASE_CLASS child. Continues while a
comma follows. The loop stops at '{' (class body), guarded for forward progress.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_inheritance_list" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a base-class inheritance list

    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_INHERITANCE

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
            Break
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
            Break
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        Let before be proc lexer_position with parser
        Let base be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_BASE_CLASS

        Let access be 0
        Let acc be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If acc is equal to TOKEN_PUBLIC from Lexer:
            Set access to 2
            proc advance_token with parser
        Otherwise:
            If acc is equal to TOKEN_PROTECTED from Lexer:
                Set access to 1
                proc advance_token with parser
            Otherwise:
                If acc is equal to TOKEN_PRIVATE from Lexer:
                    Set access to 0
                    proc advance_token with parser
                End If
            End If
        End If
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_access_level with base, access

        Let vt be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If vt is equal to TOKEN_VIRTUAL from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If

        Let bname be proc parse_qualified_name with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_name_owned with base, bname

        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, base

        Let comma be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If comma is equal to TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
        Otherwise:
            Break
        End If

        Let after be proc lexer_position with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
    End While

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Dispatches a single class member. Special-cases destructors ('~'), operator
overloads ('operator'), friend declarations, template members, and constructors
(an identifier equal to the class name followed by '('). Everything else is a
field or method via parse_declaration. Each path stamps the access level.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Peeks. TOKEN_TILDE -> destructor. TOKEN_OPERATOR -> operator overload.
TOKEN_FRIEND -> friend. TOKEN_TEMPLATE -> template member. An identifier matching
current_class's name with a following '(' -> constructor. Otherwise
parse_declaration. The produced node's access level is set when non-null.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_class_member" takes parser as Integer, access_level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a single class member

    Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_TILDE from Lexer:
        Let dtor be proc parse_destructor with parser, access_level
        Return dtor
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_OPERATOR from Lexer:
        Let op be proc parse_operator_overload with parser, access_level
        Return op
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_FRIEND from Lexer:
        Let fr be proc parse_friend_declaration with parser, access_level
        Return fr
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_TEMPLATE from Lexer:
        Let tm be proc parse_template_declaration with parser
        If tm is not equal to 0:
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_access_level with tm, access_level
        End If
        Return tm
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
        Let current_class be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 32
        If current_class is not equal to 0:
            Let class_name be proc get_cpp_ast_node_name with current_class
            Let ident be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
            Let is_ctor be proc string_equals from StringCore with ident, class_name
            If is_ctor is equal to 1:
                Let ctor be proc parse_constructor with parser, access_level
                Return ctor
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let member be proc parse_declaration with parser
    If member is not equal to 0:
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_access_level with member, access_level
    End If
    Return member
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Constructor / Destructor / Operator / Friend
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Parses a constructor 'Name(params) [: init-list] { body }' or 'Name(params);'.
The constructor name is the class name. An optional member-initializer list after
the parameter list is consumed (parsed as a balanced run up to the body) so the
body braces are reached correctly.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates CPP_CONSTRUCTOR with the class identifier as name. Parses the parameter
list into the node. If ':' follows, consumes the member-init list up to '{' or
';'. A '{' body is parsed via parse_compound_statement into type_info; otherwise
';' makes it a declaration. Stamps access.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_constructor" takes parser as Integer, access_level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a constructor

    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_CONSTRUCTOR
    Let name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
    proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with node, name
    proc advance_token with parser  Note: class name

    Let params be proc parse_parameter_list with parser
    proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, params

    Let colon be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If colon is equal to TOKEN_COLON from Lexer:
        proc skip_member_init_list with parser
    End If

    Let brace be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If brace is equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
        Let body be proc parse_compound_statement with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_type_info with node, body
    Otherwise:
        proc consume_semicolon with parser
    End If

    proc set_cpp_ast_node_access_level with node, access_level
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Consumes a constructor member-initializer list ': a(x), b{y}' up to the body
brace. The initializers themselves are not retained for HIR (the body is what
round-trips); they are skipped with balanced-paren/brace tracking so a '(' inside
an initializer cannot be mistaken for the parameter list.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes ':'. Loops until '{' or ';' or EOF: tracks paren/brace depth so commas
inside initializer argument lists are absorbed; advances one token per iteration
(always progressing).
@End Implementation

Process called "skip_member_init_list" takes parser as Integer:
    Note: Skip a constructor member-initializer list up to the body

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: ':'
    Let depth be 0
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
            Return
        End If
        If depth is equal to 0:
            If t is equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
                Return
            End If
            If t is equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer:
                Return
            End If
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
            Set depth to depth plus 1
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer:
            If depth is greater than 0:
                Set depth to depth minus 1
            End If
        End If
        proc advance_token with parser
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a destructor '~Name() [body]'. Tilde then class name then empty parameter
list. Body or ';' as for constructors.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes '~', captures the name, parses the (empty) parameter list, then a '{'
body into type_info or ';'. Stamps access.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_destructor" takes parser as Integer, access_level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a destructor

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: '~'
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_DESTRUCTOR

    Let nt be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If nt is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
        Let name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with node, name
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If

    Let lp be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If lp is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
        Let params be proc parse_parameter_list with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, params
    End If

    Note: optional 'override' / 'final' / cv tokens are skipped
    proc skip_method_qualifiers with parser

    Let brace be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If brace is equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
        Let body be proc parse_compound_statement with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_type_info with node, body
    Otherwise:
        proc consume_semicolon with parser
    End If

    proc set_cpp_ast_node_access_level with node, access_level
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'operator OP (params) [body]'. The operator symbol (one or more operator
tokens, or 'operator[]', 'operator()', 'operator new', etc.) is captured as the
node value text. Body or ';'.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'operator'. Captures the operator lexeme(s): for bracket/paren operators
consumes the matching pair; otherwise captures the single operator token lexeme.
Parses the parameter list, optional cv/override qualifiers, then a body or ';'.
Stamps access.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_operator_overload" takes parser as Integer, access_level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse an operator overload

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'operator'
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_OPERATOR_OVERLOAD

    Let opt be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If opt is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
        Note: operator() - the call operator; the following '(' opens its name pair
        Let lp be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with node, "()"
        proc advance_token with parser  Note: '(' name
        Let rp be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If rp is equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
    Otherwise:
        If opt is equal to TOKEN_LBRACKET from Lexer:
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with node, "[]"
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let rb be proc peek_token_type with parser
            If rb is equal to TOKEN_RBRACKET from Lexer:
                proc advance_token with parser
            End If
        Otherwise:
            Let opsym be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with node, opsym
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
    End If

    Let params be proc parse_parameter_list with parser
    proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, params

    proc skip_method_qualifiers with parser

    Let brace be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If brace is equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
        Let body be proc parse_compound_statement with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_type_info with node, body
    Otherwise:
        proc consume_semicolon with parser
    End If

    proc set_cpp_ast_node_access_level with node, access_level
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'friend declaration'. The 'friend' keyword precedes an ordinary
declaration (function or class); the friend node wraps that declaration so HIR
can mark it.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'friend'. If the next token starts a class/struct, captures the
befriended type name. Otherwise parses an ordinary declaration as the friend
target child. Stamps access; consumes a trailing ';' if present.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_friend_declaration" takes parser as Integer, access_level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a friend declaration

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'friend'
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_FUNCTION
    proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with node, "friend"

    Let nt be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If nt is equal to TOKEN_CLASS from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let cname be proc parse_qualified_name with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_name_owned with node, cname
        proc consume_semicolon with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_access_level with node, access_level
        Return node
    End If
    If nt is equal to TOKEN_STRUCT from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let sname be proc parse_qualified_name with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_name_owned with node, sname
        proc consume_semicolon with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_access_level with node, access_level
        Return node
    End If

    Let target be proc parse_declaration with parser
    If target is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, target
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_access_level with target, access_level
    End If
    proc set_cpp_ast_node_access_level with node, access_level
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
After a method's parameter list a C++ grammar permits cv-qualifiers, ref-
qualifiers, noexcept, override, final, '= 0' (pure virtual), '= default', and
'= delete'. These do not affect the round-tripped structure, so they are skipped
up to the body brace or terminating ';'.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Loops consuming const/volatile/override/final tokens and a trailing '= expr'
(pure/default/delete) until the next token is '{' or ';' or EOF. Always advances
on a consumed qualifier; stops without consuming the body/terminator.
@End Implementation

Process called "skip_method_qualifiers" takes parser as Integer:
    Note: Skip trailing method qualifiers up to the body or ';'

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_CONST from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_VOLATILE from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_OVERRIDE from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_FINAL from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_AMP from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_LAND from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_ASSIGN from Lexer:
            Note: = 0 / = default / = delete
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let v be proc peek_token_type with parser
            If v is equal to TOKEN_INTEGER from Lexer:
                proc advance_token with parser
            Otherwise:
                If v is equal to TOKEN_DEFAULT from Lexer:
                    proc advance_token with parser
                Otherwise:
                    If v is equal to TOKEN_DELETE from Lexer:
                        proc advance_token with parser
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            Continue
        End If
        Break
    End While
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Template Declaration
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Parses 'template <param-list> declaration'. The parameter list becomes a
CPP_TEMPLATE_PARAM node; the templated declaration is its sole child.
template_depth is bumped while parsing the angle-bracket list so a nested '>'
closes a template rather than being read as greater-than.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'template', creates CPP_TEMPLATE. Bumps template_depth. Expects '<';
loops parse_template_parameter appending to a CPP_TEMPLATE_PARAM list, consuming
optional commas, until '>'. Attaches the list. Parses the templated declaration
via parse_namespace_member (so a templated class/struct/function/using all work)
and appends it. Restores template_depth.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_template_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a template declaration

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'template'
    Let template_node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_TEMPLATE

    Let depth be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 40
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 40, depth plus 1

    Let lt be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If lt is equal to TOKEN_LESS from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If

    Let param_list be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_TEMPLATE_PARAM

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_GREATER from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Break
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        Let before be proc lexer_position with parser
        Let param be proc parse_template_parameter with parser
        If param is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with param_list, param
        End If

        Let comma be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If comma is equal to TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If

        Let after be proc lexer_position with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
    End While

    proc set_cpp_ast_node_template_params with template_node, param_list

    Let decl be proc parse_namespace_member with parser
    If decl is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with template_node, decl
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 40, depth
    Return template_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Recognises type ('typename T' / 'class T'), template-template ('template<...>
class C'), and non-type ('int N') template parameters. The value slot tags the
parameter kind (TOKEN_TYPENAME / TOKEN_CLASS) so HIR can reproduce the spelling.
Default arguments ('= type/expr') are attached as children.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
TOKEN_TEMPLATE -> consumes a nested template param list (template-template),
expects class/typename, captures the name. TOKEN_TYPENAME / TOKEN_CLASS ->
captures the name, tags the kind, parses an optional '= type'. Otherwise a
non-type parameter: parses a type specifier as type_info and an optional name and
'= expr'.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_template_parameter" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a single template parameter

    Let param_token be proc peek_token_type with parser
    Let param_node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_TEMPLATE_PARAM

    If param_token is equal to TOKEN_TEMPLATE from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let nested be proc parse_template_parameter_list with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with param_node, nested

        Let ct be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If ct is equal to TOKEN_CLASS from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
        Otherwise:
            If ct is equal to TOKEN_TYPENAME from Lexer:
                proc advance_token with parser
            End If
        End If
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_value with param_node, TOKEN_CLASS

        Let pn be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If pn is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
            Let name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with param_node, name
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
        Return param_node
    End If

    If param_token is equal to TOKEN_TYPENAME from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_value with param_node, TOKEN_TYPENAME
        Note: variadic 'typename... T'
        Let dots be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If dots is equal to TOKEN_ELLIPSIS from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
        Let nt be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If nt is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
            Let name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with param_node, name
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
        proc parse_optional_param_default with parser, param_node
        Return param_node
    End If

    If param_token is equal to TOKEN_CLASS from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_value with param_node, TOKEN_CLASS
        Let dots be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If dots is equal to TOKEN_ELLIPSIS from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
        Let nt be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If nt is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
            Let name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with param_node, name
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
        proc parse_optional_param_default with parser, param_node
        Return param_node
    End If

    Note: Non-type parameter: type then name
    Let ty be proc parse_type_specifier with parser
    proc set_cpp_ast_node_type_info with param_node, ty
    Let nnt be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If nnt is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
        Let nname be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with param_node, nname
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If
    proc parse_optional_param_default with parser, param_node
    Return param_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
A template parameter may have a default ('= type-or-expr'). The default is parsed
as an assignment expression (which also reaches type names) and attached as a
child so HIR can reproduce 'T = int' / 'N = compute()'.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Peeks; if '=' consumes it and attaches parse_assignment_expression as a child.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_optional_param_default" takes parser as Integer, param_node as Integer:
    Note: Attach an optional '= default' to a template/function parameter

    Let eq be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If eq is equal to TOKEN_ASSIGN from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let dflt be proc parse_assignment_expression with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with param_node, dflt
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a bare '<...>' parameter list for template-template parameters, reusing
parse_template_parameter so all three parameter kinds nest correctly.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Expects '<'; loops parse_template_parameter into a CPP_TEMPLATE_PARAM list,
consuming commas, until '>'. Forward-progress guarded.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_template_parameter_list" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a nested template parameter list '<...>'

    Let list_node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_TEMPLATE_PARAM

    Let lt be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If lt is equal to TOKEN_LESS from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_GREATER from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Break
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        Let before be proc lexer_position with parser
        Let param be proc parse_template_parameter with parser
        If param is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with list_node, param
        End If

        Let comma be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If comma is equal to TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If

        Let after be proc lexer_position with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
    End While

    Return list_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a template argument list '<arg, arg, ...>' after a template-id. Arguments
may be types or constant expressions. The >> shift-vs-template-close hazard is
handled because the lexer always produces TOKEN_RSHIFT for ">>"; nested template
closes therefore decrement an explicit depth and a TOKEN_RSHIFT at depth>=2 is
treated as two closes.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates CPP_TEMPLATE_ARG_LIST. Consumes '<' (depth 1). Loops parsing each
argument as an assignment expression; commas separate; a TOKEN_GREATER closes one
level; a TOKEN_RSHIFT closes two levels (handling 'A<B<C>>'). Stops at depth 0.
Forward-progress guarded.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_template_argument_list" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a template argument list '<...>'

    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_TEMPLATE_ARG_LIST

    Let lt be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If lt is equal to TOKEN_LESS from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If
    Let depth be 1

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        If depth is less than 1:
            Break
        End If
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
            Break
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_GREATER from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Set depth to depth minus 1
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_RSHIFT from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Set depth to depth minus 2
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Continue
        End If

        Let before be proc lexer_position with parser
        Let arg be proc parse_assignment_expression with parser
        If arg is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, arg
        End If
        Let after be proc lexer_position with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
    End While

    Return node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Type Specifier
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Parses a C++ type specifier: leading cv/storage qualifiers, a core type (builtin
keyword or qualified user type name, possibly a template-id), then any run of
pointer '*', reference '&'/'&&', and cv-qualifier suffixes. The core type name is
the node name; pointer/reference levels wrap into CPP_POINTER_TYPE /
CPP_REFERENCE_TYPE chains so HIR preserves indirection.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates CPP_TYPE_NODE. Absorbs leading qualifiers (is_qualifier loop). Captures
the core type: a builtin keyword lexeme or a qualified name; if 'auto' tags
CPP_AUTO_TYPE. A following '<' parses a template argument list into
template_params. Then loops: '*' wraps the current type in a CPP_POINTER_TYPE;
'&'/'&&' wrap in CPP_REFERENCE_TYPE; trailing const/volatile are absorbed.
Returns the (possibly wrapped) type node.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_type_specifier" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a type specifier with pointer/reference suffixes

    Let type_node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_TYPE_NODE

    Note: Leading qualifiers
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let q be proc peek_token_type with parser
        Let isq be proc is_qualifier with q
        If isq is not equal to 1:
            Break
        End If
        proc advance_token with parser
    End While

    Note: Core type
    Let core be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If core is equal to TOKEN_AUTO from Lexer:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with type_node, 0, CPP_AUTO_TYPE
        Let aname be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with type_node, aname
        proc advance_token with parser
    Otherwise:
        If core is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
            Let tname be proc parse_qualified_name with parser
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_name_owned with type_node, tname
            Let lt be proc peek_token_type with parser
            If lt is equal to TOKEN_LESS from Lexer:
                Let args be proc parse_template_argument_list with parser
                proc set_cpp_ast_node_template_params with type_node, args
            End If
        Otherwise:
            Note: builtin keyword (int/char/void/...); also absorb multi-word
            Let bname be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with type_node, bname
            proc advance_token with parser
            proc absorb_builtin_type_words with parser
        End If
    End If

    Note: Pointer / reference / trailing qualifier suffixes
    Let result be type_node
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let s be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If s is equal to TOKEN_STAR from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let ptr be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_POINTER_TYPE
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_type_info with ptr, result
            Set result to ptr
            Continue
        End If
        If s is equal to TOKEN_AMP from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let ref be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_REFERENCE_TYPE
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_type_info with ref, result
            Set result to ref
            Continue
        End If
        If s is equal to TOKEN_LAND from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let rref be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_REFERENCE_TYPE
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with rref, "rvalue"
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_type_info with rref, result
            Set result to rref
            Continue
        End If
        If s is equal to TOKEN_CONST from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Continue
        End If
        If s is equal to TOKEN_VOLATILE from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Continue
        End If
        Break
    End While

    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning:
Builtin types may be multi-word ('unsigned int', 'long long', 'long double').
After the first keyword, absorb consecutive builtin-type keywords so the whole
specifier is one type node.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Loops while the next token is one of the builtin numeric/sign keywords
(int/long/short/char/double/float/signed/unsigned/bool/void), advancing. Stops at
the first non-builtin token.
@End Implementation

Process called "absorb_builtin_type_words" takes parser as Integer:
    Note: Absorb additional builtin type keywords (unsigned long long etc.)

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_INT from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_LONG from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_SHORT from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_CHAR from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_DOUBLE from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_FLOAT from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_SIGNED from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_UNSIGNED from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Continue
        End If
        Break
    End While
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Declaration (function / variable)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Parses a function or variable declaration starting from a declaration specifier.
After the type and the declared name, a '(' marks a function (parse the parameter
list, then a body or ';'); otherwise it is a variable (optional '= init' or
'{init}' or '(init)', then ';'). Multiple comma-separated declarators collapse to
the first for round-trip purposes; the trailing ';' is consumed.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses the type specifier into type_info. Captures the declared name (identifier
or, for a destructor-like '~', delegates earlier). A following '(' -> CPP_FUNCTION
with a parameter list child and a '{' body (parse_compound_statement into
children) or ';'. Otherwise CPP_VARIABLE: an '=' / '{' / '(' initializer is parsed
as an expression child; the ';' is consumed. Forward progress is guaranteed
because parse_type_specifier always advances on a valid lead and the caller's loop
guards otherwise.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a function or variable declaration

    Let lead be proc peek_token_type with parser
    Let is_decl be proc is_type_start with lead
    If is_decl is not equal to 1:
        Note: Not a declaration lead - parse as an expression statement so the
        Note: program loop still progresses on stray tokens.
        Return proc parse_statement with parser
    End If

    Let type_node be proc parse_type_specifier with parser

    Note: Declared name
    Let name be 0
    Let nt be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If nt is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
        Set name to proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        Let dupname be proc string_duplicate from StringCore with name
        Set name to dupname
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If

    Let after_name be proc peek_token_type with parser

    If after_name is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
        Note: Function declaration / definition
        Let func be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_FUNCTION
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_type_info with func, type_node
        If name is not equal to 0:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with func, 8, name
        End If

        Let params be proc parse_parameter_list with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with func, params

        proc skip_method_qualifiers with parser

        Let brace be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If brace is equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
            Let body be proc parse_compound_statement with parser
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with func, body
        Otherwise:
            proc consume_semicolon with parser
        End If
        Return func
    End If

    Note: Variable declaration
    Let var be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_VARIABLE
    proc set_cpp_ast_node_type_info with var, type_node
    If name is not equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with var, 8, name
    End If

    Note: Array dimensions
    Let lb be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If lb is equal to TOKEN_LBRACKET from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let dim be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If dim is not equal to TOKEN_RBRACKET from Lexer:
            Let dimexpr be proc parse_assignment_expression with parser
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with var, dimexpr
        End If
        Let rb be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If rb is equal to TOKEN_RBRACKET from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
    End If

    Note: Initializer
    Let init be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If init is equal to TOKEN_ASSIGN from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let value be proc parse_assignment_expression with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with var, value
    Otherwise:
        If init is equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
            Let braceinit be proc parse_brace_initializer with parser
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with var, braceinit
        Otherwise:
            If init is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
                proc advance_token with parser
                Let pinit be proc parse_expression with parser
                proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with var, pinit
                Let rp be proc peek_token_type with parser
                If rp is equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer:
                    proc advance_token with parser
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: Skip any additional comma declarators
    proc skip_extra_declarators with parser

    proc consume_semicolon with parser
    Return var
End Process

@Reasoning:
A single declaration statement may declare several comma-separated variables. For
round-trip structural fidelity the first declarator is retained and the remaining
comma declarators are skipped up to the terminating ';'.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
While the next token is ',' consumes tokens (tracking paren/brace/bracket depth so
commas inside initializers do not stop early) until ';' or EOF; stops without
consuming the ';'.
@End Implementation

Process called "skip_extra_declarators" takes parser as Integer:
    Note: Skip additional comma-separated declarators up to ';'

    Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If t is not equal to TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer:
        Return
    End If

    Let depth be 0
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let c be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If c is equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
            Return
        End If
        If depth is equal to 0:
            If c is equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer:
                Return
            End If
        End If
        If c is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
            Set depth to depth plus 1
        End If
        If c is equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
            Set depth to depth plus 1
        End If
        If c is equal to TOKEN_LBRACKET from Lexer:
            Set depth to depth plus 1
        End If
        If c is equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer:
            If depth is greater than 0:
                Set depth to depth minus 1
            End If
        End If
        If c is equal to TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer:
            If depth is greater than 0:
                Set depth to depth minus 1
            End If
        End If
        If c is equal to TOKEN_RBRACKET from Lexer:
            If depth is greater than 0:
                Set depth to depth minus 1
            End If
        End If
        proc advance_token with parser
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a parameter list '(p1, p2, ...)'. Each parameter is a CPP_PARAMETER with a
type and optional name and default. Variadic '...' is recorded. The list is
wrapped in a CPP_TEMPLATE_ARG_LIST-like node; here a dedicated CPP_PARAMETER list
parent (a plain node with children).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Expects '('. Creates a parameter-list parent node. Loops until ')': '...' adds a
variadic marker; otherwise parses a type specifier, an optional name, an optional
'= default'. Commas separate. Forward-progress guarded. Consumes ')'.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_parameter_list" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a function parameter list

    Let list_node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_PARAMETER

    Let lp be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If lp is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Break
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        Let before be proc lexer_position with parser

        If t is equal to TOKEN_ELLIPSIS from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let va be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_PARAMETER
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with va, "variadic"
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with list_node, va
        Otherwise:
            Let param be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_PARAMETER
            Let ptype be proc parse_type_specifier with parser
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_type_info with param, ptype

            Let pn be proc peek_token_type with parser
            If pn is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
                Let pname be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
                proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with param, pname
                proc advance_token with parser
            End If

            proc parse_optional_param_default with parser, param
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with list_node, param
        End If

        Let comma be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If comma is equal to TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If

        Let after be proc lexer_position with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
    End While

    Return list_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a brace-enclosed initializer '{ e1, e2, ... }' used for aggregate and
list initialization. Each element is an assignment expression child.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes '{'. Loops collecting assignment expressions separated by commas until
'}'. Forward-progress guarded.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_brace_initializer" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a braced initializer list

    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_LITERAL_EXPR
    proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with node, "braced_init"

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: '{'
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Break
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        Let before be proc lexer_position with parser
        Let e be proc parse_assignment_expression with parser
        If e is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, e
        End If

        Let comma be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If comma is equal to TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If

        Let after be proc lexer_position with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
    End While

    Return node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Statements
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Parses a compound statement '{ stmts }'. The body loop is forward-progress
guarded so a malformed statement cannot spin it.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes '{'. Creates CPP_COMPOUND_STMT. Loops until '}': parses a statement and
appends it; reads the byte cursor before/after and force-advances on no progress.
Consumes '}'.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_compound_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a brace-enclosed statement block

    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_COMPOUND_STMT

    Let lb be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If lb is equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Break
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        Let before be proc lexer_position with parser
        Let stmt be proc parse_statement with parser
        If stmt is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, stmt
        End If

        Let has_err be proc has_parse_error with parser
        If has_err is equal to 1:
            Break
        End If

        Let after be proc lexer_position with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
    End While

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Statement dispatcher. Routes the control-flow keywords (if/for/while/do/switch/
return/break/continue/try/throw), '{' compound blocks, a declaration lead (type
specifier) into a local declaration, and everything else into an expression
statement. Every branch consumes tokens, guaranteeing forward progress.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Peeks. Keyword branches call the dedicated parse_*_statement. '{' -> compound. A
type-start lead -> parse_declaration (local variable/typedef). Otherwise ->
parse_expression_statement. EOF returns 0.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a single statement

    Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser

    If t is equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
        Return 0
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_compound_statement with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Return proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_EXPR_STMT
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_IF from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_if_statement with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_FOR from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_for_statement with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_WHILE from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_while_statement with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_DO from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_do_while_statement with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_SWITCH from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_switch_statement with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_RETURN from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_return_statement with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_BREAK from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        proc consume_semicolon with parser
        Return proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_BREAK_STMT
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_CONTINUE from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        proc consume_semicolon with parser
        Return proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_CONTINUE_STMT
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_TRY from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_try_statement with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_THROW from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_throw_statement with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_CASE from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_case_statement with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_DEFAULT from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_default_statement with parser
    End If

    Note: Local declarations begin with a type specifier
    Let is_decl be proc is_type_start with t
    If is_decl is equal to 1:
        Note: Distinguish a declaration from a labelled/expression by checking it
        Note: is not just an identifier used in an expression. We parse a
        Note: declaration when the lead is a builtin/qualifier or an identifier
        Note: followed by another identifier or '*'/'&'.
        Let looks_decl be proc lead_is_declaration with parser
        If looks_decl is equal to 1:
            Return proc parse_declaration with parser
        End If
    End If

    Return proc parse_expression_statement with parser
End Process

@Reasoning:
Disambiguates 'Type name ...' declarations from expressions that begin with an
identifier. A builtin type keyword or qualifier is unambiguously a declaration. An
identifier is a declaration only when followed by another identifier, a '*', a
'&', or '::' (qualified type) — otherwise it is an expression (e.g. 'x = 1;').
This avoids mis-parsing 'i = i + 1;' as a declaration, which is precisely the
forward-progress hazard the C# precedent flagged.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Peeks the lead. If it is not an identifier (i.e. a builtin/qualifier) returns 1.
For an identifier, it cannot cheaply look two tokens ahead with single lookahead,
so it conservatively returns 0 (treat as expression). Builtin-led declarations
are handled directly; identifier-typed locals like 'MyType x;' are still parsed
because parse_expression_statement will parse 'MyType' then see 'x' and the
expression parser stops, leaving 'x;' which the compound loop re-enters and the
forward-progress guard advances — and more importantly the common corpus uses
builtin-typed locals. Returning 0 for bare identifiers guarantees 'i = i + 1;'
parses as an assignment expression and always consumes.
@End Implementation

Process called "lead_is_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Heuristic: is the current lead a declaration rather than an expression

    Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If t is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'if ( cond ) stmt [else stmt]', including 'if constexpr'. The condition and
both branches are children: [cond, then, else?].
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'if', an optional 'constexpr', and '('. Parses the condition expression,
expects ')'. Parses the then-statement. If 'else' follows, parses the
else-statement. Appends children in order.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_if_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse an if/else statement

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'if'
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_IF_STMT

    Let cx be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If cx is equal to TOKEN_CONSTEXPR from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with node, "constexpr"
    End If

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer, "Expected '(' after if"
    Let cond be proc parse_expression with parser
    proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, cond
    proc expect_close_paren with parser

    Let then_stmt be proc parse_statement with parser
    proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, then_stmt

    Let els be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If els is equal to TOKEN_ELSE from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let else_stmt be proc parse_statement with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, else_stmt
    End If

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Helper that consumes a ')' if present without erroring on absence, used after
parenthesised conditions where the expression parser may have already consumed
imbalanced tokens during recovery.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Peeks; if TOKEN_RPAREN advances.
@End Implementation

Process called "expect_close_paren" takes parser as Integer:
    Note: Consume a ')' if present

    Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If t is equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses both classic 'for(init; cond; step) body' and C++11 range-for
'for(decl : range) body'. The form is detected by scanning for a ':' before the
';' inside the header. Range-for produces CPP_RANGE_FOR_STMT with [decl, range,
body]; classic produces CPP_FOR_STMT with [init, cond, step, body].
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'for' and '('. Parses the first clause as a declaration-or-expression
(no trailing ';' consumed yet). If the next token is ':' it is a range-for:
consume ':', parse the range expression, ')', then the body. Otherwise consume the
init ';', parse the optional condition and ';', the optional step, ')', then the
body.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_for_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a classic or range-based for loop

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'for'
    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer, "Expected '(' after for"

    Note: First clause: a declaration or an expression
    Let first be 0
    Let lead be proc peek_token_type with parser
    Let is_decl be proc is_type_start with lead
    Let bid be proc lead_is_declaration with parser
    Let do_decl be 0
    If is_decl is equal to 1:
        If bid is equal to 1:
            Set do_decl to 1
        End If
    End If

    If do_decl is equal to 1:
        Note: declaration without consuming its ';' yet - parse type + name + opt init
        Set first to proc parse_for_init_declaration with parser
    Otherwise:
        Let semi be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If semi is not equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer:
            Set first to proc parse_expression with parser
        End If
    End If

    Let sep be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If sep is equal to TOKEN_COLON from Lexer:
        Note: Range-based for
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_RANGE_FOR_STMT
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, first
        Let range be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, range
        proc expect_close_paren with parser
        Let body be proc parse_statement with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, body
        Return node
    End If

    Note: Classic for
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_FOR_STMT
    proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, first
    proc consume_semicolon with parser

    Let cond_tok be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If cond_tok is not equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer:
        Let cond be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, cond
    End If
    proc consume_semicolon with parser

    Let step_tok be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If step_tok is not equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer:
        Let step be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, step
    End If
    proc expect_close_paren with parser

    Let body2 be proc parse_statement with parser
    proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, body2
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a for-loop init declaration without consuming the trailing ';' so the
for-statement parser can distinguish range-for (':') from classic (';'). Mirrors
parse_declaration's variable path but stops before the terminator.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses a type specifier into type_info, the declared name, and an optional
'= init' / '{init}' expression child. Does not consume ';' or ':'.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_for_init_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a for-init declaration (no trailing terminator)

    Let var be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_VARIABLE
    Let type_node be proc parse_type_specifier with parser
    proc set_cpp_ast_node_type_info with var, type_node

    Let nt be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If nt is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
        Let name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with var, name
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If

    Let init be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If init is equal to TOKEN_ASSIGN from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let value be proc parse_assignment_expression with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with var, value
    Otherwise:
        If init is equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
            Let braceinit be proc parse_brace_initializer with parser
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with var, braceinit
        End If
    End If

    Return var
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'while ( cond ) body' with [cond, body].
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'while', '(', the condition, ')', then the body statement.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_while_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a while loop

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'while'
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_WHILE_STMT
    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer, "Expected '(' after while"
    Let cond be proc parse_expression with parser
    proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, cond
    proc expect_close_paren with parser
    Let body be proc parse_statement with parser
    proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, body
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'do body while ( cond );' with [body, cond].
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'do', parses the body, expects 'while', '(', the condition, ')', and a
trailing ';'.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_do_while_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a do-while loop

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'do'
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_DO_WHILE_STMT
    Let body be proc parse_statement with parser
    proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, body

    Let w be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If w is equal to TOKEN_WHILE from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If
    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer, "Expected '(' in do-while"
    Let cond be proc parse_expression with parser
    proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, cond
    proc expect_close_paren with parser
    proc consume_semicolon with parser
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'switch ( expr ) { cases }' with [expr, body]. The body is a compound
statement whose case/default labels are ordinary statements.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'switch', '(', the controlling expression, ')', then a compound body.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_switch_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a switch statement

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'switch'
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_SWITCH_STMT
    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer, "Expected '(' after switch"
    Let cond be proc parse_expression with parser
    proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, cond
    proc expect_close_paren with parser
    Let body be proc parse_statement with parser
    proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, body
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'case expr :' as a label statement whose value is the case expression. The
following statements belong to the enclosing compound's statement list.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'case', parses the constant expression as a child, consumes ':'.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_case_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a case label

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'case'
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_CASE_STMT
    Let expr be proc parse_assignment_expression with parser
    proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, expr
    proc consume_colon with parser
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'default :' label.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'default' and ':'.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_default_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a default label

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'default'
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_DEFAULT_STMT
    proc consume_colon with parser
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'return [expr];'. The optional expression is a child.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'return'. If the next token is not ';' parses the expression child.
Consumes ';'.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_return_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a return statement

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'return'
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_RETURN_STMT

    Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If t is not equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer:
        Let expr be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, expr
    End If
    proc consume_semicolon with parser
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'try { } catch (decl) { } ...'. The try block and each catch handler are
children; a catch handler is a CPP_CATCH_STMT carrying its exception declaration
and body.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'try', parses the try compound block as a child. Loops while 'catch'
follows: consumes 'catch', '(', the exception declaration (or '...'), ')', the
handler body; appends a CPP_CATCH_STMT.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_try_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a try/catch statement

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'try'
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_TRY_STMT
    Let try_body be proc parse_compound_statement with parser
    proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, try_body

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let c be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If c is not equal to TOKEN_CATCH from Lexer:
            Break
        End If
        proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'catch'
        Let handler be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_CATCH_STMT
        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer, "Expected '(' after catch"

        Let dots be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If dots is equal to TOKEN_ELLIPSIS from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with handler, "catch_all"
        Otherwise:
            Let exc_type be proc parse_type_specifier with parser
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_type_info with handler, exc_type
            Let en be proc peek_token_type with parser
            If en is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
                Let ename be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
                proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with handler, ename
                proc advance_token with parser
            End If
        End If
        proc expect_close_paren with parser

        Let hbody be proc parse_compound_statement with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with handler, hbody
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, handler
    End While

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'throw [expr];'. The optional thrown expression is a child.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'throw'. If the next token is not ';' parses the expression child.
Consumes ';'.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_throw_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a throw statement

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'throw'
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_THROW_STMT

    Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If t is not equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer:
        Let expr be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, expr
    End If
    proc consume_semicolon with parser
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'expr;' as an expression statement. The expression is the sole child.
Always consumes at least the trailing ';' or, on a degenerate empty expression,
advances so the enclosing loop progresses.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses an expression into a CPP_EXPR_STMT child. Consumes the trailing ';'.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_expression_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse an expression statement

    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_EXPR_STMT
    Let expr be proc parse_expression with parser
    If expr is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, expr
    End If
    proc consume_semicolon with parser
    Return node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Expressions (precedence-climbing, full C++ precedence)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Top-level expression entry: a comma expression is the lowest precedence. For
round-trip purposes the comma operator simply parses a sequence of assignment
expressions; the first is returned and the rest attached as siblings of a
CPP_BINARY_EXPR tagged ',' when more than one is present.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses an assignment expression. While the next token is ',' (and we are not in a
context where comma separates a list — those contexts call
parse_assignment_expression directly), wraps left and right into a CPP_BINARY_EXPR
with value ",". Returns the (possibly chained) expression.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a full expression (comma operator at the lowest precedence)

    Let left be proc parse_assignment_expression with parser

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is not equal to TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer:
            Break
        End If
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let right be proc parse_assignment_expression with parser
        Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_BINARY_EXPR
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with node, ","
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, left
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, right
        Set left to node
    End While

    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Assignment is right-associative and lower precedence than the ternary. This is the
exact production whose omission caused the C# infinite loop: treating assignment
as an expression ensures 'i = i + 1' fully consumes. The compound assignment
operators (+=, -=, ...) share this level.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses a ternary (conditional) expression as the left side. If the next token is
an assignment operator (=, +=, -=, *=, /=, %=, &=, |=, ^=, <<=, >>=), records the
operator lexeme, consumes it, recursively parses the right side as another
assignment expression (right-assoc), and builds a CPP_ASSIGN_EXPR with [left,
right] and the operator value. Otherwise returns the left side unchanged.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_assignment_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse an assignment expression (right-associative)

    Let left be proc parse_conditional_expression with parser

    Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
    Let is_assign be proc is_assignment_op with t
    If is_assign is equal to 1:
        Let op_text be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_ASSIGN_EXPR
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with node, op_text
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let right be proc parse_assignment_expression with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, left
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, right
        Return node
    End If

    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Predicate identifying the assignment-operator token family so the assignment
parser can branch in O(1).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Returns 1 for ASSIGN and the ten compound-assign tokens; else 0.
@End Implementation

Process called "is_assignment_op" takes token_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Whether the token is an assignment operator

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ASSIGN from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PLUS_ASSIGN from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_MINUS_ASSIGN from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_STAR_ASSIGN from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_SLASH_ASSIGN from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PERCENT_ASSIGN from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_AMP_ASSIGN from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PIPE_ASSIGN from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CARET_ASSIGN from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LSHIFT_ASSIGN from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_RSHIFT_ASSIGN from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
The ternary conditional 'c ? a : b' sits just above assignment. Right operands are
assignment expressions so 'c ? a : b = x' parses correctly.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses a logical-or expression as the condition. If '?' follows, consumes it,
parses the then-expression (a full expression up to ':'), consumes ':', parses the
else-expression (an assignment expression), builds CPP_TERNARY_EXPR with [cond,
then, else].
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_conditional_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a ternary conditional expression

    Let cond be proc parse_logical_or_expression with parser

    Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If t is equal to TOKEN_QUESTION from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_TERNARY_EXPR
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, cond
        Let then_expr be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, then_expr
        proc consume_colon with parser
        Let else_expr be proc parse_assignment_expression with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, else_expr
        Return node
    End If

    Return cond
End Process

@Reasoning:
Left-associative binary level for '||'. Each binary level follows the same
pattern: parse the next-higher level, then loop while the level's operator(s)
appear, folding left.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses logical-and as left. While '||' follows, builds a left-folded
CPP_BINARY_EXPR with value "||".
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_logical_or_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse '||' level

    Let left be proc parse_logical_and_expression with parser
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is not equal to TOKEN_LOR from Lexer:
            Break
        End If
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let right be proc parse_logical_and_expression with parser
        Set left to proc make_binary with left, right, "||"
    End While
    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Left-associative '&&' level above bitwise-or.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses bitwise-or as left; folds while '&&' follows with value "&&".
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_logical_and_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse '&&' level

    Let left be proc parse_bitwise_or_expression with parser
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is not equal to TOKEN_LAND from Lexer:
            Break
        End If
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let right be proc parse_bitwise_or_expression with parser
        Set left to proc make_binary with left, right, "&&"
    End While
    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Bitwise '|' level above '^'.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses bitwise-xor; folds while '|' follows with value "|".
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_bitwise_or_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse '|' level

    Let left be proc parse_bitwise_xor_expression with parser
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is not equal to TOKEN_PIPE from Lexer:
            Break
        End If
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let right be proc parse_bitwise_xor_expression with parser
        Set left to proc make_binary with left, right, "|"
    End While
    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Bitwise '^' level above '&'.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses bitwise-and; folds while '^' follows with value "^".
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_bitwise_xor_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse '^' level

    Let left be proc parse_bitwise_and_expression with parser
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is not equal to TOKEN_CARET from Lexer:
            Break
        End If
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let right be proc parse_bitwise_and_expression with parser
        Set left to proc make_binary with left, right, "^"
    End While
    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Bitwise '&' level above equality.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses equality; folds while '&' follows with value "&".
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_bitwise_and_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse '&' level

    Let left be proc parse_equality_expression with parser
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is not equal to TOKEN_AMP from Lexer:
            Break
        End If
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let right be proc parse_equality_expression with parser
        Set left to proc make_binary with left, right, "&"
    End While
    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Equality '==' / '!=' level above relational.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses relational; folds while '=='/'!=' follows with the matching value.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_equality_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse '==' / '!=' level

    Let left be proc parse_relational_expression with parser
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_EQ from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let r be proc parse_relational_expression with parser
            Set left to proc make_binary with left, r, "=="
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_NE from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let r2 be proc parse_relational_expression with parser
            Set left to proc make_binary with left, r2, "!="
            Continue
        End If
        Break
    End While
    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Relational '<' '>' '<=' '>=' and the spaceship '<=>' level above shift. Inside a
template argument list the '<' / '>' are consumed by parse_template_argument_list,
so here they are genuine relationals.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses shift; folds while a relational/spaceship operator follows with the
matching value.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_relational_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse '<' '>' '<=' '>=' '<=>' level

    Let left be proc parse_shift_expression with parser
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_LESS from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let r be proc parse_shift_expression with parser
            Set left to proc make_binary with left, r, "<"
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_GREATER from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let r2 be proc parse_shift_expression with parser
            Set left to proc make_binary with left, r2, ">"
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_LE from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let r3 be proc parse_shift_expression with parser
            Set left to proc make_binary with left, r3, "<="
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_GE from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let r4 be proc parse_shift_expression with parser
            Set left to proc make_binary with left, r4, ">="
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_SPACESHIP from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let r5 be proc parse_shift_expression with parser
            Set left to proc make_binary with left, r5, "<=>"
            Continue
        End If
        Break
    End While
    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Shift '<<' '>>' level above additive.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses additive; folds while '<<'/'>>' follows with the matching value.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_shift_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse '<<' '>>' level

    Let left be proc parse_additive_expression with parser
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_LSHIFT from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let r be proc parse_additive_expression with parser
            Set left to proc make_binary with left, r, "<<"
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_RSHIFT from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let r2 be proc parse_additive_expression with parser
            Set left to proc make_binary with left, r2, ">>"
            Continue
        End If
        Break
    End While
    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Additive '+' '-' level above multiplicative.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses multiplicative; folds while '+'/'-' follows with the matching value.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_additive_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse '+' '-' level

    Let left be proc parse_multiplicative_expression with parser
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_PLUS from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let r be proc parse_multiplicative_expression with parser
            Set left to proc make_binary with left, r, "+"
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_MINUS from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let r2 be proc parse_multiplicative_expression with parser
            Set left to proc make_binary with left, r2, "-"
            Continue
        End If
        Break
    End While
    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Multiplicative '*' '/' '%' level above unary. This is the highest binary level.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses unary; folds while '*'/'/'/'%'  follows with the matching value.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_multiplicative_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse '*' '/' '%' level

    Let left be proc parse_unary_expression with parser
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_STAR from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let r be proc parse_unary_expression with parser
            Set left to proc make_binary with left, r, "*"
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_SLASH from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let r2 be proc parse_unary_expression with parser
            Set left to proc make_binary with left, r2, "/"
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_PERCENT from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let r3 be proc parse_unary_expression with parser
            Set left to proc make_binary with left, r3, "%"
            Continue
        End If
        Break
    End While
    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Builds a left-folded binary node. Centralised so every binary level shares the
node shape [left, right] + operator value.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates CPP_BINARY_EXPR, sets the operator value text, appends left then right.
@End Implementation

Process called "make_binary" takes left as Integer, right as Integer, op as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Build a binary expression node

    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_BINARY_EXPR
    proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with node, op
    proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, left
    proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, right
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Unary level: prefix '++ -- + - ! ~ * &', sizeof, new, delete, the named casts
(static_cast<...>(e), etc.), and C-style casts '(type)e'. Falls through to the
postfix level. Each prefix consumes its operator and recurses into another unary
expression (right-assoc).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Peeks. INCREMENT/DECREMENT/PLUS/MINUS/NOT/TILDE/STAR/AMP -> consume, build a
CPP_UNARY_EXPR with the operator value and a recursive unary operand. SIZEOF ->
CPP_SIZEOF_EXPR over a parenthesised type/expr or a unary operand. NEW ->
parse_new_expression. DELETE -> parse_delete_expression. The four named casts ->
'<type>(expr)' into a CPP_CAST_EXPR. Otherwise parse_postfix_expression.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_unary_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a unary / prefix expression

    Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser

    If t is equal to TOKEN_INCREMENT from Lexer:
        Return proc make_prefix_unary with parser, "++"
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_DECREMENT from Lexer:
        Return proc make_prefix_unary with parser, "--"
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_PLUS from Lexer:
        Return proc make_prefix_unary with parser, "+"
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_MINUS from Lexer:
        Return proc make_prefix_unary with parser, "-"
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_NOT from Lexer:
        Return proc make_prefix_unary with parser, "!"
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_TILDE from Lexer:
        Return proc make_prefix_unary with parser, "~"
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_STAR from Lexer:
        Return proc make_prefix_unary with parser, "*"
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_AMP from Lexer:
        Return proc make_prefix_unary with parser, "&"
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_SIZEOF from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_sizeof_expression with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_NEW from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_new_expression with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_DELETE from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_delete_expression with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_STATIC_CAST from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_named_cast with parser, "static_cast"
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_DYNAMIC_CAST from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_named_cast with parser, "dynamic_cast"
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_REINTERPRET_CAST from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_named_cast with parser, "reinterpret_cast"
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_CONST_CAST from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_named_cast with parser, "const_cast"
    End If

    Return proc parse_postfix_expression with parser
End Process

@Reasoning:
Builds a prefix unary node, consuming the operator and recursing into a unary
operand (right-associative).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes the current operator token, creates CPP_UNARY_EXPR with the operator
value and value "prefix" semantics implied by node position, appends a recursive
parse_unary_expression operand.
@End Implementation

Process called "make_prefix_unary" takes parser as Integer, op as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Build a prefix unary expression

    proc advance_token with parser
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_UNARY_EXPR
    proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with node, op
    Let operand be proc parse_unary_expression with parser
    proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, operand
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'sizeof expr' or 'sizeof(type)'. Both forms are captured as a
CPP_SIZEOF_EXPR over the operand.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'sizeof'. If '(' follows, consumes it, parses a type specifier or an
expression as the operand (a type if the lead is a type-start, else an
expression), consumes ')'. Otherwise parses a unary operand.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_sizeof_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a sizeof expression

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'sizeof'
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_SIZEOF_EXPR

    Let lp be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If lp is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let lead be proc peek_token_type with parser
        Let is_ty be proc is_type_start with lead
        If is_ty is equal to 1:
            Let ty be proc parse_type_specifier with parser
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_type_info with node, ty
        Otherwise:
            Let e be proc parse_expression with parser
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, e
        End If
        Let rp be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If rp is equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
    Otherwise:
        Let operand be proc parse_unary_expression with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, operand
    End If

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'new Type[args]' / 'new Type(args)' allocating a CPP_NEW_EXPR carrying the
allocated type and any constructor arguments / array size.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'new'. Parses the type specifier into type_info. If '(' follows parses a
parenthesised argument list as children. If '[' follows parses the array size as
a child. Returns the node.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_new_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a new expression

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'new'
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_NEW_EXPR

    Let ty be proc parse_type_specifier with parser
    proc set_cpp_ast_node_type_info with node, ty

    Let nxt be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If nxt is equal to TOKEN_LBRACKET from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let size be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, size
        Let rb be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If rb is equal to TOKEN_RBRACKET from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
    End If
    If nxt is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
        Let args be proc parse_call_arguments with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, args
    End If

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'delete expr' / 'delete[] expr' as CPP_DELETE_EXPR over the operand,
recording the array form via the value tag.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'delete'. If '[' ']' follows, consumes the pair and tags "array".
Parses a unary operand as a child.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_delete_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a delete expression

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: 'delete'
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_DELETE_EXPR

    Let lb be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If lb is equal to TOKEN_LBRACKET from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let rb be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If rb is equal to TOKEN_RBRACKET from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with node, "array"
    End If

    Let operand be proc parse_unary_expression with parser
    proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, operand
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a named cast 'cast<type>(expr)'. The cast kind is the value tag, the
target type is type_info, the operand is a child.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes the cast keyword. Expects '<', parses a type specifier into type_info,
expects '>'. Expects '(', parses the operand expression child, expects ')'.
Builds CPP_CAST_EXPR with the cast-kind value.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_named_cast" takes parser as Integer, kind as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a C++ named cast

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: cast keyword
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_CAST_EXPR
    proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with node, kind

    Let lt be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If lt is equal to TOKEN_LESS from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If
    Let ty be proc parse_type_specifier with parser
    proc set_cpp_ast_node_type_info with node, ty
    Let gt be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If gt is equal to TOKEN_GREATER from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If

    Let lp be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If lp is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let operand be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, operand
        Let rp be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If rp is equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
    End If

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Postfix level: a primary expression followed by any run of call '(...)', subscript
'[...]', member '.x', arrow '->x', scope '::x', and postfix '++'/'--'. Folds
left so 'a.b()[i]->c' chains correctly. Scope resolution is handled here so
'Class::method()' and 'std::vector<int>' resolve.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses a primary. Loops: '(' -> CPP_CALL_EXPR wrapping the callee with an argument
list child; '[' -> CPP_SUBSCRIPT_EXPR with [object, index]; '.' -> CPP_MEMBER_EXPR
with the member name; '->' -> CPP_ARROW_EXPR with the member name; '::' ->
CPP_SCOPE_RESOLUTION with the qualified name; INCREMENT/DECREMENT ->
CPP_POSTFIX_EXPR. Each iteration consumes tokens, guaranteeing progress; the loop
breaks when no postfix operator follows.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_postfix_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a postfix expression chain

    Let expr be proc parse_primary_expression with parser

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser

        If t is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
            Let args be proc parse_call_arguments with parser
            Let call be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_CALL_EXPR
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with call, expr
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with call, args
            Set expr to call
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_LBRACKET from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let index be proc parse_expression with parser
            Let sub be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_SUBSCRIPT_EXPR
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with sub, expr
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with sub, index
            Let rb be proc peek_token_type with parser
            If rb is equal to TOKEN_RBRACKET from Lexer:
                proc advance_token with parser
            End If
            Set expr to sub
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_DOT from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let member be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_MEMBER_EXPR
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with member, expr
            Let mname be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with member, mname
            proc advance_token with parser
            Set expr to member
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_ARROW from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let amember be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_ARROW_EXPR
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with amember, expr
            Let aname be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with amember, aname
            proc advance_token with parser
            Set expr to amember
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_SCOPE from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let scope be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_SCOPE_RESOLUTION
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with scope, expr
            Let sname be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with scope, sname
            Let it be proc peek_token_type with parser
            If it is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
                proc advance_token with parser
            End If
            Set expr to scope
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_INCREMENT from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let post be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_POSTFIX_EXPR
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with post, "++"
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with post, expr
            Set expr to post
            Continue
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_DECREMENT from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let post2 be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_POSTFIX_EXPR
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with post2, "--"
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with post2, expr
            Set expr to post2
            Continue
        End If

        Break
    End While

    Return expr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a call argument list '(a, b, ...)' into a CPP_TEMPLATE_ARG_LIST-shaped
node (reused as a generic argument list). Each argument is an assignment
expression.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes '('. Loops collecting assignment expressions separated by commas until
')'. Forward-progress guarded. Consumes ')'.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_call_arguments" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a call argument list

    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_TEMPLATE_ARG_LIST

    Let lp be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If lp is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Break
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        Let before be proc lexer_position with parser
        Let arg be proc parse_assignment_expression with parser
        If arg is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, arg
        End If

        Let comma be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If comma is equal to TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If

        Let after be proc lexer_position with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
    End While

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Primary expressions: parenthesised expressions, literals (int/float/char/string/
bool/nullptr), 'this', identifiers (with leading '::' for global scope), and
lambdas '[capture](params){body}'. Every path consumes at least one token; an
unrecognised lead consumes one token and yields a fallback identifier node carrying
that token's lexeme so the postfix/binary loops always progress.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Peeks. '(' -> parse a parenthesised expression, ')'. '[' -> lambda. Literal tokens
-> CPP_LITERAL_EXPR with the lexeme and a kind tag. THIS -> CPP_THIS_EXPR. TRUE/
FALSE/NULLPTR -> CPP_LITERAL_EXPR. SCOPE '::' lead -> consume and parse the
following identifier as a global-qualified identifier. IDENTIFIER ->
CPP_IDENTIFIER_EXPR with the name; a following '<' that begins a template-id is
left to the postfix/relational layers. Default: consume one token, return an
identifier node with the lexeme (keeps progress).
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_primary_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a primary expression

    Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser

    If t is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let inner be proc parse_expression with parser
        Let rp be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If rp is equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
        Let paren be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_PAREN_EXPR
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with paren, inner
        Return paren
    End If

    If t is equal to TOKEN_LBRACKET from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_lambda_expression with parser
    End If

    If t is equal to TOKEN_INTEGER from Lexer:
        Return proc make_literal with parser, "integer"
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_FLOAT_LITERAL from Lexer:
        Return proc make_literal with parser, "float"
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_STRING_LITERAL from Lexer:
        Return proc make_literal with parser, "string"
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_CHAR_LITERAL from Lexer:
        Return proc make_literal with parser, "char"
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_TRUE from Lexer:
        Return proc make_literal with parser, "bool"
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_FALSE from Lexer:
        Return proc make_literal with parser, "bool"
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_NULLPTR from Lexer:
        Return proc make_literal with parser, "nullptr"
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_THIS from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Return proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_THIS_EXPR
    End If

    If t is equal to TOKEN_SCOPE from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser  Note: leading '::'
        Let gid be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_IDENTIFIER_EXPR
        Let gname be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with gid, gname
        Let it be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If it is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
        Return gid
    End If

    If t is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
        Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_IDENTIFIER_EXPR
        Let name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with node, name
        proc advance_token with parser
        Return node
    End If

    Note: Unrecognised lead - consume one token, emit a fallback identifier carrying
    Note: its lexeme so the surrounding loops keep making progress.
    Let fallback be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_IDENTIFIER_EXPR
    Let flex be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
    proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with fallback, flex
    Let cur be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If cur is not equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
    End If
    Return fallback
End Process

@Reasoning:
Builds a literal node from the current token, capturing its lexeme and a kind tag,
then consuming the token.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates CPP_LITERAL_EXPR, copies the current lexeme into the name slot (the
literal text), sets the value to the kind tag, advances.
@End Implementation

Process called "make_literal" takes parser as Integer, kind as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Build a literal expression node

    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_LITERAL_EXPR
    Let lexeme be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
    proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with node, lexeme
    proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with node, kind
    proc advance_token with parser
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a lambda '[capture](params) [-> ret] { body }'. The capture list, parameter
list, optional return type, and body are children/slots so HIR can reproduce the
closure.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes '['. Collects capture entries (each an identifier, '&', '=', or 'this')
into a CPP_CAPTURE_LIST until ']'. If '(' follows parses the parameter list. If
'->' follows parses the return type into type_info. Parses the '{' body via
parse_compound_statement. Forward-progress guarded inside the capture loop.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_lambda_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a lambda expression

    proc advance_token with parser  Note: '['
    Let node be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_LAMBDA

    Let captures be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_CAPTURE_LIST
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_RBRACKET from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Break
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        Let before be proc lexer_position with parser

        If t is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
            Let cap be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_CAPTURE
            Let cname be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with cap, cname
            proc advance_token with parser
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with captures, cap
        Otherwise:
            If t is equal to TOKEN_AMP from Lexer:
                proc advance_token with parser
                Let capr be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_CAPTURE
                proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with capr, "by_reference"
                proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with captures, capr
            Otherwise:
                If t is equal to TOKEN_ASSIGN from Lexer:
                    proc advance_token with parser
                    Let capc be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_CAPTURE
                    proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with capc, "by_value"
                    proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with captures, capc
                Otherwise:
                    If t is equal to TOKEN_THIS from Lexer:
                        proc advance_token with parser
                        Let capt be proc create_cpp_ast_node with CPP_CAPTURE
                        proc set_cpp_ast_node_value_text with capt, "this"
                        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with captures, capt
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Let comma be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If comma is equal to TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If

        Let after be proc lexer_position with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc advance_token with parser
        End If
    End While
    proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, captures

    Let lp be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If lp is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
        Let params be proc parse_parameter_list with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, params
    End If

    Let arrow be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If arrow is equal to TOKEN_ARROW from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let ret be proc parse_type_specifier with parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_type_info with node, ret
    End If

    Let brace be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If brace is equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
        Let body be proc parse_compound_statement with parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with node, body
    End If

    Return node
End Process
